JOHANNESBURG - Peggy Whitson has officially broken the record for cumulative time in space by an American astronaut.She has surpassed astronaut Jeff Williams mark of 534 days set in 2016.READ: NASA astronaut casts lone vote from spaceLast month, Whitson made history when she floated outside the International Space Station breaking the record for the most spacewalks by a woman.Whitson, 57, is making her eighth career spacewalk, surpassing the record of seven previously held by American Suni Williams.The goal of the six-and-a-half hour spacewalk is to continue upgrading the International Space Station for the arrival of commercial spaceships in the years to come. eNCA